<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">14. Willis, Victoria Jane. <em>A Bibliography on Color and Light: Theory and Application. </em>Monticello, IL: Council of Planning Librarians, 1977. Exchange Bibliography #1426. 15 pp.</p><p class="annot">More than 100 titles are listed in this unannotated bibliography. Publication dates range from 1925 to the mid-1970s. Many of the classic color theory books are included, making this a useful beginning source for anyone doing general color research. The bibliography lacks an explanation of its scope and limitations.</p></div>
